<item>
            <title>[LU-17489] fix &apos;lfs getname&apos; ioctl breakage</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17489</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Fix &lt;tt&gt;ioctl()&lt;/tt&gt; incompatibility introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16634&quot; title=&quot;Null pointer dereference in lustre_set_wire_obdo&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16634&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16634&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was caused by the removal of the explicit &lt;tt&gt;ioctl(OBD_IOC_GETNAME_OLD)&lt;/tt&gt; fallback in &lt;tt&gt;llapi_file_fget_lov_uuid()&lt;/tt&gt; without replacing the existing &lt;tt&gt;ioctl(OBD_IOC_GETDTNAME)&lt;/tt&gt; call with &lt;tt&gt;llapi_ioctl(OBD_IOC_GETDTNAME)&lt;/tt&gt; that handles this compatibility mapping internally.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
